{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778380068029,"sessionID":"ses_1f04f82f9ffeDDrOkGVKv0nDx8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_U1FW29tAfBIi6QhH9dV9RYAh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I added the requested GI epithelium and lamina propria terms, with logical definitions tying each layer to the relevant gut segment.\n+\n*** Add File: PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added 11 new UBERON terms requested in issue #3495:\n+\n+- Epithelium terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, and sigmoid colon.\n+- Lamina propria terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, sigmoid colon, stomach, caecum, and rectum.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+These terms support consistent annotation and searching of GI mucosal layers across the requested gut segments. Epithelium terms use `intestinal epithelium` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant colon segment, as requested. Lamina propria terms use `lamina propria` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant gut segment, without duplicating the `part_of` axiom as a relationship.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Read imported issue context from `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Checked for existing exact requested terms before adding new ones.\n+- Verified parent terms and IDs for intestinal epithelium, lamina propria, and the requested GI segments.\n+- Used `anatomyPartOfAnatomy`-style genus-differentia logical definitions.\n+- Added definition citations, synonym provenance, contributor/date metadata, `created_by`, and `term_tracker_item` links.\n+- Validated syntax with `robot convert`.\n+- Validated logical consistency with `robot reason --reasoner ELK`.\n+- Committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` locally.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n+\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I added the requested GI epithelium and lamina propria terms, with logical definitions tying each layer to the relevant gut segment.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added 11 new UBERON terms requested in issue #3495:\n+\n+- Epithelium terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, and sigmoid colon.\n+- Lamina propria terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, sigmoid colon, stomach, caecum, and rectum.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+These terms support consistent annotation and searching of GI mucosal layers across the requested gut segments. Epithelium terms use `intestinal epithelium` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant colon segment, as requested. Lamina propria terms use `lamina propria` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant gut segment, without duplicating the `part_of` axiom as a relationship.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Read imported issue context from `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Checked for existing exact requested terms before adding new ones.\n+- Verified parent terms and IDs for intestinal epithelium, lamina propria, and the requested GI segments.\n+- Used `anatomyPartOfAnatomy`-style genus-differentia logical definitions.\n+- Added definition citations, synonym provenance, contributor/date metadata, `created_by`, and `term_tracker_item` links.\n+- Validated syntax with `robot convert`.\n+- Validated logical consistency with `robot reason --reasoner ELK`.\n+- Committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` locally.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"ISSUE_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+I added the requested GI epithelium and lamina propria terms, with logical definitions tying each layer to the relevant gut segment.\n","additions":3,"deletions":0},{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","relativePath":"PR_COMMENTS.md","type":"add","patch":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+Added 11 new UBERON terms requested in issue #3495:\n+\n+- Epithelium terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, and sigmoid colon.\n+- Lamina propria terms for ascending colon, transverse colon, descending colon, sigmoid colon, stomach, caecum, and rectum.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+These terms support consistent annotation and searching of GI mucosal layers across the requested gut segments. Epithelium terms use `intestinal epithelium` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant colon segment, as requested. Lamina propria terms use `lamina propria` as the genus with `part_of` the relevant gut segment, without duplicating the `part_of` axiom as a relationship.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- Read imported issue context from `__issue_context__.json`.\n+- Checked for existing exact requested terms before adding new ones.\n+- Verified parent terms and IDs for intestinal epithelium, lamina propria, and the requested GI segments.\n+- Used `anatomyPartOfAnatomy`-style genus-differentia logical definitions.\n+- Added definition citations, synonym provenance, contributor/date metadata, `created_by`, and `term_tracker_item` links.\n+- Validated syntax with `robot convert`.\n+- Validated logical consistency with `robot reason --reasoner ELK`.\n+- Committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` locally.\n+\n+@dragon-ai-agent\n","additions":23,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778380068018,"end":1778380068025}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_033395583d395e3b0169ffed1e752c8196b9b4ce74bb99d592"}},"id":"prt_e0fb63f260012ek5AXEXQVD0E1","sessionID":"ses_1f04f82f9ffeDDrOkGVKv0nDx8","messageID":"msg_e0fb6300d001Fg2SpYjU8Yr1C9"}}
